# Copy to .env.local and fill in to serve book covers from your own static host
# instead of hotlinking gutenberg.org (which throttles and drops connections).
#
# 1. npm run mirror:covers        # downloads + optimizes covers into covers/
# 2. upload the covers/ contents to a static host (jsDelivr off a GitHub repo,
#    Cloudflare R2, etc.)
# 3. set this to the URL of the folder that directly holds the <id>.webp files
#
# Example (jsDelivr off a GitHub repo named focus-reader-covers):
# VITE_COVER_BASE=https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/youruser/focus-reader-covers@v1
VITE_COVER_BASE=
